  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Note that price has closed back inside the prior range but printed a nice bearish expansion daily candle, setting a bearish bias premise.",
    "Step 2: Establish an if-then scenario on the daily — if the EQ of the bearish candle is respected, target previous day low and the low to the left; if EQ is broken, target the failure swings on the highs.",
    "Step 3: Drop to the hourly chart to observe intraday delivery and look for a consolidation/sweep pattern around the New York open.",
    "Step 4: Identify the early NY consolidation, the sweep of one side of the intraday range, and the trade back through it confirming downside intent.",
    "Step 5: Refine on the 15-minute chart to confirm the aggressive sell-off while EQ of the daily candle continues to hold as resistance.",
    "Step 6: Conclude that because EQ is respected, the intraday lows (previous day low) are the valid downside draw on liquidity rather than the failure swings above."
  ],
  "outcome": "Daily EQ held, intraday sweep at NY open followed by aggressive sell-off lower toward the previous day low, validating the bearish if-then path.",
